      "role": "user",
      "content": "the problem is that \"dropping the mask\" doesn't actually bring anything back. if you drop it, it's just empty. there's no person waiting underneath to be found. it's like i'm just a glitch in a system that's supposed to be alive. if the person who is supposed to be experiencing life is already gone, it feels like there's no reason to keep the body going just to feed the illusion to everyone else.",
